y unlike any other.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice Olympiccompetitors\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The grand procession, which takes place on July 26, has been crafted from the mind of artistic director Thomas Jolly.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.999981605014933, \"rank\": 1.6863091088400512e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The grand procession\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"the mind\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Olympics opening and closing ceremonies tend to take place in a decorated stadium, for the first time ever, the anticipated affair will be held along the River Seine in Paris, France, in a program meant to last three hours and 45 minutes.\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5907095154006895e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999995111466, \"rank\": 4.3520292252971093e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"a decorated stadium\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"the anticipated affair\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"a program\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 836}, {\"ngram\": \"three hours\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"45 minutes\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why?\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because the 42-year-old creative director wanted it so.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 42-year-old creative director\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In conversation withVogue, Jolly explained how he reimagined the traditional segments of the opening ceremony - the artistic segment, the delegation segment, and the protocol segment - and spun them into an entirely new event.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"conversation withVogue\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"the traditional segments\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"the artistic segment\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"the delegation segment\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"the protocol segment\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"an entirely new event\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have decided to interweave them for an evening lasting three hours and 45 minutes, where countries from around the world alternate, parading in a dozen tableaux,\\\" he told the outlet in an interview published on July 18.\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an evening\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1218}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"a dozen tableaux\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlet\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Like athletes passing between the Pont d'Austerlitz and the Pont d'I\\u00e9na, this grand fresco draws its inspiration from all the historical sites they traverse.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\", \"score\": 0.9999997127829787, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont d'I\\u00e9na\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont d'Austerlitz\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"this grand fresco\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"its inspiration\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"all the historical sites\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And what fabulous inspiration it is!\\\"\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what fabulous inspiration\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the highly-anticipated 2024 ParisOlympics,Voguespoke with Jolly about his two-year creative process preparing for the distinguished spectacle.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the highly-anticipated 2024 ParisOlympics\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"Voguespoke\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"his two-year creative process\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"the distinguished spectacle\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The popular French actor chose to start the opening festivities at 7:30 pm CEST just before the sun sets, mainly for ecological purposes.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.990793279621467, \"rank\": 0.00891073087948133, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening festivities\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"7:30 pm CEST\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"the sun sets\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"ecological purposes\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the host city is Paris, Jolly found motivation in its exquisite foundation - the buildings, the bridges, the sidewalks, and the water - all emblematic of the city's rich history.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 2065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5907095154006895e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the host city\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"motivation\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"its exquisite foundation\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"the buildings\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"the bridges\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"the sidewalks\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's rich history\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea was to preserve what already existed, but enliven it with the work of 3,000 artists from across several mediums like dance, music, comedy, and more.\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2074}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2141}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000 artists\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"several mediums\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2186}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2197}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"comedy\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everything is respectful of the environment in which we are set,\\\" he explained.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everything\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"the environment\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I call this ceremony, 'La grande c\\u00e9l\\u00e9bration de notre humanit\\u00e9 partag\\u00e9e,' the grand celebration of our shared humanity!\\\"\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2427, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this ceremony\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"La grande c\\u00e9l\\u00e9bration de notre humanit\\u00e9 partag\\u00e9e\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"the grand celebration\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"our shared humanity\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While such an opening ceremony would likely be rehearsed to ensure a perfect delivery, Jolly is not planning to do a single practice - something he is unfamiliar with, coming from the theater world.\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect delivery\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"a single practice\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"the theater world\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Despite all our preparations, we must remember that, in order to maintain its confidentiality, this ceremony will never be fully rehearsed,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all our preparations\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2690}, {\"ngram\": \"its confidentiality\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"this ceremony\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The goal is for everyone to discover the spectacle simultaneously!\\\"\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The goal\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2788}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2804}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacle\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for what in-person and at-home viewers can expect, Jolly revealed that the first boat will emerge under the Pont d'Austerlitz.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2978, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2870}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2908}, {\"ngram\": \"the first boat\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pont d'Austerlitz\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 2977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly collaborated with several other individuals to design the remarkable production.\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several other individuals\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"the remarkable production\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Le\\u00efla Slimani, an award-winning novelist; Damien Gabriac, a playwright; Fanny Herrero, a screenwriter; and Patrick Boucheron, a historian, played a massive role in the opening ceremony's construction.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3067, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le\\u00efla_Slimani\", \"score\": 0.9999999991300683, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le\\u00efla Slimani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le\\u00efla_Slimani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le\\u00efla_Slimani\"}, {\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriac,_Aveyron\", \"score\": 0.8010054874943173, \"rank\": 0.1249999999999922, \"text\": \"Gabriac\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriac,_Aveyron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriac,_Aveyron\"}, {\"begin\": 3139, \"end\": 3144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"score\": 0.9999999998931344, \"rank\": 1.0703417895886425e-10, \"text\": \"Fanny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.9929541319120434, \"rank\": 0.006475138936867363, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boucheron\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http:/